 Since $XY=YZ,$ then $\triangle XYZ$ is isosceles. Draw altitude $YW$ from $Y$ to $W$ on $XZ.$ Altitude $YW$ bisects the base $XZ$ so that $$XW=WZ=\frac{30}{2}=15,$$as shown. [asy] draw((0,0)--(30,0)--(15,-8)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
